    <h3 id="api-reference">API Reference</h3>
    <div class="api-reference">
        <p>The <code>tooltip</code> option accepts either a string (for simple tooltips) or a hash with the following properties:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><code>content</code> (String) - The text content of the tooltip</li>
            <li><code>position</code> (String, optional) - Position of the tooltip relative to the button. Options:
                <ul>
                    <li><code>top</code> (default), <code>bottom</code>, <code>left</code>, <code>right</code></li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li><code>align</code> (String, optional) - Alignment of the tooltip. Options:
                <ul>
                    <li><code>start</code>, <code>center</code> (default), <code>end</code></li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li><code>trigger</code> (String, optional) - How the tooltip is triggered. Options:
                <ul>
                    <li><code>hover</code> (default) - Shows on mouseenter/focus</li>
                    <li><code>click</code> - Shows on click</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li><code>delay</code> (Hash, optional) - Delay times for showing/hiding the tooltip
                <ul>
                    <li><code>show</code> (Number) - Delay before showing (default: 0)</li>
                    <li><code>hide</code> (Number) - Delay before hiding (default: 0)</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li><code>offset</code> (Number, optional) - Space between button and tooltip (default: 8)</li>
            <li><code>theme</code> (String/Hash, optional) - Tooltip theme. Options:
                <ul>
                    <li>String: <code>light</code> (default), <code>dark</code>, <code>transparent</code></li>
                    <li>Hash: Custom theme with:
                        <ul>
                            <li><code>custom: { color: String, background: String }</code></li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li><code>size</code> (String, optional) - Size of the tooltip. Options:
                <ul>
                    <li><code>sm</code>, <code>md</code> (default), <code>lg</code></li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li><code>arrow</code> (Boolean, optional) - Whether to show an arrow pointer (default: false)</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

